profile_positions.description:
Ritchie Bros. Auctioneers is the international recognized worldwide leader in unreserved Auctions, selling a broad range of used and unused industrial equipment including equipment utilized in the construction, transportation, material handling, mining, forestry, petroleum, marine, real estate and agricultural industries. They have over 110 offices in more than 25 countries, including 37 auction sites worldwide.

Main responsibilities:
	Compliance:  complete and maintain the legal requirements and documentation of the new European Head office and all European venues. Structure and maintain all Corporate files, report to Canadian Head office;
	Organizing and maintaining the operational side of the office, i.e. office supplies, cleaning, security & maintenance of building; Responsible for secretaries and reception;
	Maintaining all European Assets / Contracts / Insurances regarding personnel, liability, property, cars, etc.
	Assisting the European Director of Finance with compiling financial overviews, agenda, correspondence, travel/hotel requirements, meetings and ad-hoc projects, taking care of his appointments and outstanding actions in his absence.
